
Function: ZILEVAL

Syntax:   (ZILEVAL arg1 arg2 arg3)

 arg1 (required, evaluated) - an atom or proper list.
 arg2 (required, evaluated) - an evaluation environment.
 arg3 (required, evaluated) - T or NIL.

Returns:

 The result of evaluating arg1, with the evalation environment
 specified by arg2 being used to resolve variable bindings.

Processing:

 See EVAL.

 arg3 is T if this evaluation is to be considered at "top level",
 otherwise NIL.

Errors signaled:

 See EVAL.

Notes:

 ZILEVAL is the internal ZIL function that underlies EVAL.  It
 permits you to pass a complete evaluation environment to EVAL.
 Not for general use.

